  <h3>Statistics</h3>
  <p style="font-family:Trebuchet MS;">11 teens die every day as a result of texting while driving</p>
<p style="font-family:Trebuchet MS;">The National Safety Council reports that cell phone use while driving leads to 1.6 million crashes each year</p>
<p style="font-family:Trebuchet MS;">Nearly 330,000 injuries occur each year from accidents caused by texting while driving</p>
<p style="font-family:Trebuchet MS;">Texting while driving is 6x more likely to cause an accident than driving drunk</p>
<p style="font-family:Trebuchet MS;">21% of teen drivers involved in fatal accidents were distracted by their cell phones</p>
<p style="font-family:Trebuchet MS;">The Virginia Tech Transportation Institute found that text messaging creates a crash risk 23 times worse than driving while not distracted</p>
<p style="font-family:Trebuchet MS;">1 out of every 4 car accidents in the United States is caused by texting and driving</p>
<p style="font-family:Trebuchet MS;">Teens who text while driving spend approximately 10% of their driving time outside of their lane</p>
<p style="font-family:Trebuchet MS;">In 2014, 3,179 people were killed, and 431,000 were injured in motor vehicle crashes involving distracted drivers </p>
